postcontent: This listing is for a G.I. war trophy lot. Included is a browning FN model 1910 pistol… 32 caliber. The G.I. was stationed in the Aleutian Islands. The US ARMY was securing the island...flushing out small pockets of Japanese soldiers.  Often the Japanese would rush the US forces in a futile attempt to hold on...surrender was not an option for most...only death could bring honor to their family.  This pistol was fired at the US ARMY soldier, he was hit in the leg. The six other GI's in the group fired their machine guns, and killed the Japanese officer....they  recovered this pistol from his body. There is a letter authorizing the G.I. to keep the pistol as a WAR TROPHY.  The holster, Japanese, is also included. This GI was given a Purple Heart for his injury... that is also included.  To watch the GI was wearing that day, with army issued tropical strap, is included in the Lot.
